stories.text:
Hi HN,

I'm excited to build something for the new Stripe Apps marketplace and landed on the idea of a tool to query your Stripe data using natural language instead of SQL (e.g. asking "How many customers are on annual subscriptions?" rather than writing a SQL query). Seems like it could be useful for users who don't know how to code in particular.

This isn't a Show HN as I'm at the discovery stage here so I just thought I'd ask here if people would envision this being useful in their companies.

Quick landing page here: https://cashquery-marketing-site.vercel.app/
